  <!-- Help Window -->
  <StyleExpand_HelpTitle>RimTalk StyleExpand - Help</StyleExpand_HelpTitle>
  <StyleExpand_HelpQuickStart>== Quick Start ==</StyleExpand_HelpQuickStart>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStep1>1. Place .txt files in the Styles folder (click 'Open Folder')</StyleExpand_HelpStep1>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStep2>2. Click 'Scan Styles' to detect new files</StyleExpand_HelpStep2>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStep3>3. Select a style from the list</StyleExpand_HelpStep3>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStep4>4. Click 'Chunk Style' to process the style</StyleExpand_HelpStep4>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStep5>5. Done! The style will be used in RimTalk conversations</StyleExpand_HelpStep5>
  <StyleExpand_HelpApiConfig>== API Configuration ==</StyleExpand_HelpApiConfig>
  <StyleExpand_HelpApiUrl>- Vector API URL: Your embedding API endpoint</StyleExpand_HelpApiUrl>
  <StyleExpand_HelpApiSupport>- Supports OpenAI-compatible APIs (Ollama, OpenAI, etc.)</StyleExpand_HelpApiSupport>
  <StyleExpand_HelpApiModel>- Model: The embedding model name (e.g., bge-small-zh)</StyleExpand_HelpApiModel>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleFiles>== Style Files ==</StyleExpand_HelpStyleFiles>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleOne>- One .txt file = one style</StyleExpand_HelpStyleOne>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleName>- Filename becomes the style name</StyleExpand_HelpStyleName>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleContent>- File content is used for style examples</StyleExpand_HelpStyleContent>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleSize>- Recommended size: Chinese 5,000-50,000 chars | English 3,000-30,000 words</StyleExpand_HelpStyleSize>
  <StyleExpand_HelpStyleSizeNote>- Larger files will work but take longer to process</StyleExpand_HelpStyleSizeNote>
  <StyleExpand_HelpChunking>== Chunking ==</StyleExpand_HelpChunking>
  <StyleExpand_HelpChunkWhat>- Chunks text into smaller pieces</StyleExpand_HelpChunkWhat>
  <StyleExpand_HelpChunkEmbed>- Computes embeddings for each chunk</StyleExpand_HelpChunkEmbed>
